Name: pyundo
Version: 0.1
Summary: A task flow in Python with do and undo
Home-page: https://github.com/xgfone/pyundo
Author: xgfone
Author-email: xgfone@126.com
License: UNKNOWN
Description: pyundo
        ======
        
        A task flow in Python with ``do`` and ``undo``.
        
        Example
        =======
        
        ::
        
          from __future__ import print_function
          from pyundo import TaskBase, LineFlow
        
        
          class Task(TaskBase):
              def __init__(name):
                  self.name = name
        
              def do(self):
                  print("Do the task: {0}".format(self.name))
        
              def undo(self):
                  print("Undo the task: {0}".format(self.name))
        
        
          def main():
              flow = LineFlow()
              flow.add(Task("task1"))
              flow.add(Task("task2"))
              flow.add(Task("task3"))
              flow.execute()
        
        
          if __name__ == "__main__":
              main()
        
        
